    "summary": "I am a researcher and topic expert with extensive experience in East and Central Africa, India, and the Global South in general. My topic expertise relates to innovation processes, digital development, smallholder agriculture, Africa/Global South, technology adoption, co-creation, responsible design, and responsible research and innovation. My recent research activities have focused on digital innovations in agriculture, especially agricultural extension, digital inclusion, and co-creation of digital services. I have a PhD degree with a dissertation titled 'More than what meets the eye: Factors and processes that shape the design and use of digital agricultural advisory and decision support in Africa'. \n\nAs a researcher I am interested in co-design and participatory design and research, specifically in the context of digital technologies and services in the Global South. Another research interest is responsible design, research, and innovation, and the broader impact of digitalization in Africa's agricultural sector. \nI have (co)authored various peer reviewed articles, book-chapters and policy documents, and presented my work in international conferences, webinars, and seminars. I am currently guest editor in chief for NJAS.\n\nPreviously I worked on diverse projects in Africa and India, covering topics like multi-stakeholder platforms, citizen science, cooking and lighting with renewable energy sources, and adoption and scaling of innovations. Beyond being a researcher, I am an experienced facilitator of interactive processes using diverse methods. \n\nExpertise and research interests: \n- Human/User Centred Design\n- Participatory and action research\n- Social and digital inclusion\n- Complex (agricultural) problems\n- Digital agriculture and digital development\n- Connective and collective action\n- East and Central Africa\n- African (banana) farming systems\n- Multi-stakeholder processes, innovation platforms\n- Socio-technical systems\n- Adoption and scaling of innovations\n- Sustainable energy solutions",
